---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Delete your DraftRight account" description="How to delete your DraftRight account and what data is removed.">
  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 text-gray-300">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Delete your DraftRight account</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-10">
      Last updated: 2026-05-03
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      DraftRight (operated by Tan Nguyen) lets you delete your account and the
      data associated with it at any time. This page describes how to request
      deletion, what gets deleted, and what is retained for how long.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3">Delete in the app (instant, self-service)</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      In the DraftRight app, open the
      <span class="text-white">Settings</span> tab &rarr;
      <span class="text-white">Account</span> &rarr;
      <span class="text-white">Delete Account</span>, then confirm. Your account
      and associated data are permanently deleted right away &mdash; no email,
      no waiting period.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3">Prefer email?</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      If you no longer have the app installed, email
      <a href="mailto:support@draftright.info" class="text-brand-400 underline">support@draftright.info</a>
      from the address you used to sign up, with the subject line
      <span class="text-white">&ldquo;Delete my account&rdquo;</span>. We process
      these within <span class="text-white">7 business days</span> and reply with
      confirmation once your data is removed.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3">What gets deleted</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 mb-4">
      <li>Your account record (email, name, hashed password)</li>
      <li>Any active or past subscription state</li>
      <li>Rewrite history and logs associated with your account</li>
      <li>All extension tokens (mobile keyboard / share extension auth)</li>
      <li>Any social-login linkage (Google, Facebook, TikTok)</li>
      <li>Stored email-verification and password-reset tokens</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3">What is retained, and for how long</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
      <li>
        <span class="text-white">Anonymized usage statistics</span> — indefinitely.
        After deletion, these are no longer linked to your identity.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-white">Payment records</span> — up to 7 years where
        required by tax compliance laws of the operator&rsquo;s jurisdiction.
        Records contain transaction amounts and dates only; not personal
        identifiers beyond what tax law mandates.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-white">Security audit logs</span> — 90 days after
        deletion, for investigation of fraud or abuse. Then permanently removed.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-white">Backups</span> — encrypted backups may contain
        a copy of your data for up to 30 days after deletion before being
        rotated out.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3">Questions</h2>
    <p>
      Anything not covered here, email
      <a href="mailto:support@draftright.info" class="text-brand-400 underline">support@draftright.info</a>
      or see the <a href="/privacy" class="text-brand-400 underline">privacy policy</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
